When you open the registration page, a request is made to the blockchain, which generates a new Wallet ID and Wallet key. Next, the user fills necessary fields and clicks on the registration button. At the same time, the system writes the new user to the database, assigning him the identifier obtained after generating the hash:<br/><br><code>const confirmationToken = uuid(); 
const base64ConfirmationToken = Buffer.from(confirmationToken).toString('base64'); 
crypto.createHash('sha256').update( \${publicKey}:${privateKey}`).digest('hex')`;</code><br/><br/>Next, the user needs to wait for an email and confirm his account.<br/><br><code>async send({to, subject, message}){ 
    return this.transporter.sendMail({ 
        from:  \ 'MedPoints ' <${this.config.auth.user}>`,` 
        to, 
        subject, 
        html: message, 
    }); 
}</code><br/><br/> Authorization takes place only by Wallet ID and Wallet key. The system checks the validity of the keys by re-generating the hash and checking its existence in the database.<br/><br><code>const id = utils.createUserId(publicKey, privateKey); 
const user = await authDAL.getUserById(id); 
</code><br/><br/>The user receives error messages, if any: <br><br><code>if(!user){ 
    throw new Error('USER_NOT_EXIST'); 
}<br/> 
if(!user.confirmed){ 
    throw new Error('USER_NOT_CONFIRMED'); 
}</code>

The search bar is available on all pages of the site. Searching is possible in clinics, services, doctors, pharmacies and drugs reference. Among drugs implemented an alphabetical search, thanks to which we get only drugs whose names begin with certain characters.<br><br><code>query.name = {$regex: \${name}`, $options: 'i'};`</code><br><br>Any search query goes in indexed database, which greatly improves the speed of displaying search results.<br>In addition, each clinic has its own location and it is possible to find all clinics in a specific country or city. The location is determined automatically but there is always the opportunity to choose another city from the list to view a list of clinics related only to this city.<br><br><code>if (parameters.filter && parameters.filter.city === 'home') {
    const {
        location,
    } = req.cookies;

if (location) {
    const locationObject = JSON.parse(location);
        parameters.filter.city = locationObject.origin;
    }
}

let url = queryPersistant.applyRequestQueryParameters(parameters, \${API_URL}/api/hospitals`);`

const request = await axios.get(url);</code>

Added functionality for uploading documents to your personal account. To do this, click "Add record" and select a maximum of 10 files, each with a size of no more than 1MB. Available formats: doc, pdf, txt, jpg, jpeg, png, xml. The following files are sent to the server. Indexed in the database and available in the "Records" section.<br><br>Duplicate files will be automatically deleted.<br>To view the gallery there is a preview.<br>Files are downloaded using the multer module and stored on the server.<br>First they are placed in a temporary folder:<br><br><code>const storage = multer.diskStorage({
  destination: (req, file, cb) => {
    cb(null, tempPath);
  },
  filename: (req, file, cb) => {
    cb(null, `${path.parse(file.originalname).name}-${Date.now()}${path.extname(file.originalname)}`);
  }
});
const upload = multer({ storage: storage });</code><br><br>Further, they are distributed in permanent folders, depending on the username:<br><br><code>const dirPath = `./uploads/${MedPoints_PublicKey}`;
for (const file of req.files) {
    fs.renameSync(path.join(file.destination, file.filename), path.join(dirPath, file.filename));
}</code><br><br>Validation is available on either client or server sides:<br><br><code>if (file.size > 1000000) {
    return this.remove();
}
if (!fileTypes.includes(file.type)) {
    return this.remove();
}
if (addedFiles.length > 9) {
    return this.remove();
}
if (addedFiles.find(el => el.name === file.name)) {
    return this.remove();
}</code>

Attachment of downloadable documents to referrals to a doctor was done. To do this was created the uploads table in the database, in which the parameters of each downloaded document are placed in the following form:<br><br><code>publicKey
transactionId
fullname
filename
timestamp
extension</code><br><br>If the document is not bound to a direction, then <br><br><code>transactionId = noTransaction</code><br>To interact with the database, the API was changed. Separate methods have been added for obtaining a list of documents by the user's publicKey, and for adding a new document.<br><br><code>exports.getUploads = async function(filter){
  const collection = this.mongo.collection(collectionName);
  let uploads = await collection.find(filter).toArray();
  return uploads;
}

exports.addUpload = async function(upload){
  const collection = this.mongo.collection(collectionName);
  await collection.insert(upload);
};</code><br><br>When you go to the page with records, the site sends a request to the database, receives documents associated with this user and displays them in order. First tied to booking, then separate. And on the page with the additions of documents, you can choose in which direction to attach documents, or leave them separate.<br><br><code>&lt;ul class="list-group"&gt;

    {{#each transactions as |transaction|}}

    &lt;li&gt;
        &lt;label class="custom-control custom-radio"&gt;
            &lt;input name="radioTransaction" type="radio" class="custom-control-input" data-transaction-id="{{transaction.Id}}"&gt;
            &lt;span class="custom-control-indicator"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
            &lt;span class="custom-control-description"&gt;{{transaction.Date}}, &lt;a href="/clinics/{{transaction.ClinicInfo.id}}"&gt;{{transaction.ClinicInfo.name}}&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
        &lt;/label&gt;
    &lt;/li&gt;

    {{/each}}

    &lt;li&gt;
        &lt;label class="custom-control custom-radio"&gt;
            &lt;input name="radioTransaction" type="radio" class="custom-control-input" data-transaction-id="noTransaction" checked&gt;
            &lt;span class="custom-control-indicator"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
            &lt;span class="custom-control-description"&gt;{{localize req 'account.addRecordPage.aloneRecord'}}&lt;/span&gt;
        &lt;/label&gt;
    &lt;/li&gt;

&lt;/ul&gt;</code>

Filters were made by type of documents and date. For documents attached to booking, this is the date of the appointment with the doctor, and for individual documents, this is the date they were uploaded to the server.<br><br>The filter by date does not allow you to set the value From more than To, and vice versa:<br><br><code>let from = (this.dataset.side === "from") 
? new Date(event.target.value)
: new Date(document.querySelector(`.date-picker[data-type="${this.dataset.type}"][data-side="from"]`).value);

let to = (this.dataset.side === "from") 
? new Date(document.querySelector(`.date-picker[data-type="${this.dataset.type}"][data-side="to"]`).value)
: new Date(event.target.value);

if (from > to) {
    this.value = event.target.defaultValue;

    if (this.dataset.side === "from") {
        from = new Date(this.value);
    } else {
        to = new Date(this.value);
    }
}</code><br><br>Dates are sorted separately for related documents and not:<br><br><code>for (const transaction of filteredTransactions) {
    if (!dates.linked.from) {
        dates.linked.from = transaction.Date;
    }
    if (!dates.linked.to) {
        dates.linked.to = transaction.Date;
    }

    const transTime = moment(transaction.Date, 'YYYY-MM-DD').unix();
    const fromTime = moment(dates.linked.from, 'YYYY-MM-DD').unix();
    const toTime = moment(dates.linked.to, 'YYYY-MM-DD').unix();

    if (transTime < fromTime) {
        dates.linked.from = transaction.Date;
    } else if (transTime > toTime) {
        dates.linked.to = transaction.Date;
    }
}</code><br><br>By analogy, a filter by date was added for referrals to the doctor on the main page of the <a href="/account">account</a>

The functionality of adding a specific campaign to your account has been implemented. You need to go to <a href="/foundation">foundation</a>, select open campaigns, and click list funds opposite the chosen case. After that, a request will be sent to the server with the following parameters:<br><br><code>const data = {
    name: this.closest(".row").querySelector(".case-link").textContent,
    link: this.closest(".row").querySelector(".case-link").pathname,
    treatment: this.closest(".row").querySelector(".treatment").textContent,
};</code><br><br>The server will add an entry to the database through the API, sending it:<br><br><code>await axios.post(`${API_URL}/api/foundations`, {
    publicKey: MedPoints_PublicKey,
    transactionId: generateId(48),
    name: name,
    link: link,
    treatment: treatment,
    timestamp: Date.now(),
});</code><br><br>Now in your account in the <a href="/account/foundations">foundations</a> will be displayed new entry.

Added the ability to remove Clinic, Doctor or Pharmacy from favorites. To do this, a request to the database is sent:<br><br><code>const request = await axios.post(`${API_URL}/api/users/${MedPoints_PublicKey}/${MedPoints_PrivateKey}/favorites/remove`, data);</code><br><br>
In which the document is deleted:<br><br><code>await collection.update({
    _id: id
  }, {
    $pull: {
      favorites: {
        id: {$eq: favorite.id}
      }
    }
});</code>

Added functionality of account demo balance. In the transaction list <a href="/account/balance">balance</a>, only recharge is available. Implemented through the database.<br><br>You can replenish the balance using the Add balance button. Only data from 1 to 1000 can be entered. Data is rounded. If not valid, then nothing happens. Data is sent to the database:<br><br><code>if (req.body) {
    const { amount } = req.body;
    if (amount) {
        if (isNaN(parseFloat(amount))) {
            return res.status(200).end();
        }

        const sum = Math.round(parseFloat(amount));

        if (sum <= 0 || sum > 1000) {
            return res.status(200).end();
        }

        await axios.post(`${API_URL}/api/tokens`, {
            publicKey: MedPoints_PublicKey,
            transactionId: generateId(48),
            name: "Balance replenishment",
            type: "add",
            balanceUSD: sum,
            timestamp: Date.now(),
        });
    }
}</code><br><br>Summation of the balance is carried out by the database API. Database query:<br><br><code>const tokensCountResponse = await axios.get(`${API_URL}/api/tokens/${MedPoints_PublicKey}/count`);
const tokensCount = tokensCountResponse.data.result.count / 0.001;</code><br><br>DB processing:<br><br><code>const tokens = await exports.getTokens({publicKey: publicKey});
  let tokensCount = 0;
  for (const token of tokens) {
    tokensCount += token.balanceUSD;
  }
  return {
    count: tokensCount,
};</code><br><br>Transactions on the <a href="/account/balance">balance</a> page are implemented similarly to Assistant fund cases.
